.welcome
  h1
    | Rundeck Ruby Client
    small<
      | A Ruby wrapper around the Rundeck API.

  p
    | This library will strive to achieve reliable coverage of the Rundeck API.
      Please submit an issue if you find a bug and feel free to submit a pull
      request to contribute fixes or new features.

  p
    | Initial versions of this gem do not achieve 100% coverage of the Rundeck
      API. However, there is sufficient support for the primary endpoints and
      many users will not miss the features at this point. However, if you
      require support for specific endpoints sooner please submit an issue
      indicating which endpoints. I will keep requests in mind when planning
      future feature support and each release will include more endpoint
      support until there is 100% coverage.

  p
    | The layout and the code in this library is inspired by
    a< href="https://github.com/NARKOZ/gitlab" target="_blank" NARKOZ/gitlab
    | . NARKOZ does a fantastic job of keeping
      code simple and achieving API feature parity.

  p
    | Note: This guide is geared more toward entry-level users.
      If you are a more advanced user you may find the
    a<> href="http://rubydoc.info/gems/rundeck/frames" target="_blank"
      | Technical Documentation (RDoc)
    | more helpful.

