  h2 Rundeck API Reference

  p
    | The Rundeck API reference
      is a great resource because this library is a pretty thin
      wrapper around Rundeck's API. This makes it very flexible, but also means
      a lot of the parameters/options are not explicitly defined as
      method parameters. Many API options will need to be expressed via the
    code<>
      | options
    | hash. See the
    a<> href="overview"
      | Overview
    | page for more information.

  a.btn.btn-primary type="button" href="http://rundeck.org/docs/api/" target="_blank"
    | Rundeck API Reference



  h2 Installation

  | Add this line to your application's Gemfile or gemspec:

  pre
    | # Gemfile
      gem 'rundeck', '~> x.x.x'

      # gemspec
      spec.add_runtime_dependency 'rundeck', '~> x.x.x'

  | Then execute:
  pre
    | bundle install

  hr

  | Or install it yourself as:
  pre
    | gem install rundeck

  h2 Configuration
  | Require the rundeck gem:
  pre
    | require 'rundeck'

  hr

  code< endpoint
  | and
  code<> api_token
  | are required configuration parameters.
  code<> user_agent
  | is optional and defaults to 'Rundeck Ruby Gem {gem_version}':

  p
  pre
    | # Environment Variables (Recommended!)
      export RUNDECK_ENDPOINT=https://rundeck.example.com
      export RUNDECK_API_TOKEN=super_secret

  pre
    | # Ruby
      Rundeck.endpoint = 'https://rundeck.example.com'
      Rundeck.api_token = 'super_secret'
      Rundeck.user_agent = 'Custom User Agent'

  pre
    | # Ruby with multiple clients
      client1 = Rundeck.client(endpoint: 'https://rundeck.example.com',
                               api_token: 'super_secret',
                               user_agent: 'Custom User Agent')
      client2 = Rundeck.client(endpoint: 'https://rundeck2.example.com',
                               api_token: 'super_secret2')

  pre
    | # Ruby on Rails
      Rundeck.configure do |config|
        config.endpoint       = 'https://rundeck.example.com'
        config.api_token      = 'super_secret'
        config.user_agent     = 'Custom User Agent'
      end

